goals.rationale: This visualization will help us compare the yield of each variety and identify which one has the highest yield on average.

goals.visualization: Line chart of yield by year
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify any trends or patterns in yield over time.

goals.question: Which variety has the highest yield at each site?
goals.visualization: Stacked bar chart of yield by variety and site
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify which variety performs the best at each site and if there are any consistent patterns across sites.

code:
```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['variety'])['yield'].mean().reset_index()
    plt.bar(data['variety'], data['yield'], color='green')
    plt.xlabel('Variety')
    plt.ylabel('Yield')
    plt.title('What is the average yield of each variety?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data.boxplot(column='yield', by='site', figsize=(10,6))
    plt.title('How does the yield vary across different sites?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Site')
    plt.ylabel('Yield')
    plt.suptitle('')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['yield'], bins=20, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['yield'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['yield'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['yield'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['yield'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Yield')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of yield across all samples?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by=['year'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['year'], data['yield'], color='blue', linewidth=2)
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Yield')
    ax.set_title('How does the yield vary over time?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.show()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(['site', 'yield'], ascending=[True, False])
    data = data.groupby(['site']).head(1)
    data = data[['site', 'variety', 'yield']]
    data = data.pivot(index='site', columns='variety', values='yield')
    ax = data.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True, figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.set_xlabel('Site')
    ax.set_ylabel('Yield')
    ax.set_title('Which variety has the highest yield at each site?')
    ax.legend(title='Variety', bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
